Vision — Camp NAC Enrollment Site
The One Job
Get parents of kids ages 3–15 in Bucks County, PA (and surrounding areas) to submit an enrollment inquiry within the next 2–3 weeks before summer 2025 enrollment closes.
Everything on this site — every headline, every section, every animation — serves that single conversion goal.
---
Client Context
Camp NAC is an established summer camp in Horsham, Pennsylvania. Voted Best Summer Camp in Bucks County. They offer:
13-week flexible summer schedule (attend as few or as many weeks as you like)
75+ themed camp programs for kids ages 3–15
Activities spanning arts, STEM, cooking, sports, NACventures (outdoor adventure), teen programs, and Early Learners (ages 3–5)
A "custom build your summer" model — no minimum weeks, flexible scheduling, multi-week discounts
Schools Out Camp (SOC) and Village Farm Camp as specialty offerings
A strong community reputation — real families, real testimonials
The agency: Xovera (xovera.io) — building this site as part of a GHL CRM setup for Camp NAC. This microsite will capture leads that flow into a GHL subaccount pipeline.
---
Audience
Primary: Parents of children ages 3–15, Bucks County PA and surrounding suburbs
Secondary: Grandparents or guardians making enrollment decisions
What they care about:
Safety and trust (established, reputable camp)
Flexibility (doesn't lock them into a full summer)
Variety (something for every kid's interest)
Value (multi-week discounts, quality programming)
Urgency is real — spots fill up and they know it
What they DON'T want:
Generic camp language that sounds like every other camp
Long confusing forms
Uncertainty about what happens after they submit
---
Tone & Voice
Warm but confident — this is an established camp that earns trust
Direct — parents are busy; get to the point fast
Slightly playful — it's a camp, there should be energy and joy
Never corporate, never salesy, never hollow ("Your child's adventure awaits!" = trash)
Good headline example: "75 camps. Build the summer your kid actually wants."  
Bad headline example: "Unlock a World of Adventure at Camp NAC!"
---
Design Direction
The site should feel modern, editorial, and distinctly NOT like a typical camp site (which tends toward cheesy stock photos, rainbow colors, and Comic Sans energy).
Reference aesthetic: premium youth brand — think Patagonia kids meets a well-funded STEM academy. Clean, confident, with moments of warmth.
Full design spec is in `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`.
